That's why I persuaded them.

267
00:15:56,460 --> 00:15:58,860
I thought that was a brilliant move.

268
00:15:58,960 --> 00:16:01,400
If all of the mammoth breads were sweet,

269
00:16:01,470 --> 00:16:04,169
I would have gotten sick of it toward the end.

270
00:16:04,170 --> 00:16:05,570
This way, everything tasted delicious.

271
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:07,340
I enjoyed them very much.

272
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:08,440
Thank you.

273
00:16:09,140 --> 00:16:10,769
As for the savory one,

274
00:16:10,770 --> 00:16:14,779
did Jin Seo find the level of its saltiness today?

275
00:16:14,780 --> 00:16:15,850
Yes.

276
00:16:16,610 --> 00:16:20,579
The balance of flavors and scents were very nice.

277
00:16:20,580 --> 00:16:25,160
It felt like a chef had made it, so I was surprised.

278
00:16:25,490 --> 00:16:28,959
Also, they suit the theme well.

279
00:16:28,960 --> 00:16:30,559
I enjoyed eating them.

280
00:16:30,560 --> 00:16:34,530
I liked how you conveyed what you intended successfully.

281
00:16:35,230 --> 00:16:36,629
I think it was the best compliment...

282
00:16:36,630 --> 00:16:39,169
one could give to a baker.

283
00:16:39,170 --> 00:16:40,939
I was very happy.

284
00:16:40,940 --> 00:16:43,639
It instilled a bit of hope.

285
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:47,280
If we win second place, we can all advance.

286
00:17:09,230 --> 00:17:10,230
It's spicy.

287
00:17:16,470 --> 00:17:17,510
It's too salty.

288
00:17:18,410 --> 00:17:21,410
The Gen MZ's preference is hard to grasp, indeed.

289
00:17:22,210 --> 00:17:23,549
Isn't it too salty?

290
00:17:23,550 --> 00:17:25,080
- Pardon? - Isn't it too salty?

291
00:17:26,780 --> 00:17:28,120
Isn't the taste too strong?

292
00:17:32,290 --> 00:17:35,030
This is how I want to put it.

293
00:17:35,330 --> 00:17:36,730
"Do you want sweetness?"

294
00:17:36,760 --> 00:17:38,530
"I'll make it even sweeter."

295
00:17:38,630 --> 00:17:41,030
"Do you want saltiness? I'll make it even saltier."

296
00:17:41,470 --> 00:17:42,869
That's how I feel it.

297
00:17:42,870 --> 00:17:45,739
Compared to my preference,

298
00:17:45,740 --> 00:17:49,109
it was a bit too much.

299
00:17:49,110 --> 00:17:51,069
As for the overall balance of the food,

300
00:17:51,070 --> 00:17:53,440
I thought it was a bit salty.

301
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:58,649
When you put many ingredients in a bread,

302
00:17:58,650 --> 00:18:00,349
it's all or nothing.

303
00:18:00,350 --> 00:18:02,420
It's either totally well-balanced...

304
00:18:02,450 --> 00:18:03,820
or a mess.

305
00:18:06,390 --> 00:18:09,089
I was very worried too.

306
00:18:09,090 --> 00:18:11,529
I thought, "Gosh. It's topping after topping."

307
00:18:11,530 --> 00:18:13,629
I was very concerned.

308
00:18:13,630 --> 00:18:16,969
Despite my concerns, the one with chocolate,

309
00:18:16,970 --> 00:18:19,869
the savory one, and the dacquoise...

310
00:18:19,870 --> 00:18:22,739
keep a good balance among the ingredients.

311
00:18:22,740 --> 00:18:24,479
I thought it was okay.

312
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:25,779
It gave me a good impression.

313
00:18:25,780 --> 00:18:28,079
There's one thing I didn't like.

314
00:18:28,080 --> 00:18:30,349
The one with the chicken tasted good,

315
00:18:30,350 --> 00:18:31,720
but it was so soggy.

316
00:18:32,220 --> 00:18:33,379
Yes. It was soggy.

317
00:18:33,380 --> 00:18:35,719
So when I was eating what's already soggy,

318
00:18:35,720 --> 00:18:37,619
it was a little disappointing.

319
00:18:37,620 --> 00:18:41,730
Other than that, the balance of them all was beyond expectations.

320
00:18:43,360 --> 00:18:45,530
I thought it was tough.

321
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:50,530
I knew some would like it and some wouldn't.

322
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:52,370
But it was all right.

323
00:18:52,470 --> 00:18:54,869
It's because I think...

324
00:18:54,870 --> 00:18:58,040
people who like such a scent will like it.

325
00:18:59,310 --> 00:19:02,610
Now, Team Workout Day, please come to the front.

326
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:05,420
- Let's go. - Good luck, Chef.

327
00:19:05,720 --> 00:19:06,720
For Pie.

328
00:19:10,790 --> 00:19:12,390
It could be tasty if it was done right.

329
00:19:14,260 --> 00:19:15,730
All three products are pies.

330
00:19:22,230 --> 00:19:23,570
Gosh. They're so pretty.

331
00:19:29,340 --> 00:19:30,669
Hello.

332
00:19:30,670 --> 00:19:34,680
Our theme was the Workout Day.

333
00:19:34,910 --> 00:19:38,580
We've prepared pies for people who work out.

334
00:19:38,720 --> 00:19:42,120
So we've become Team For Pie. Thank you.

335
00:19:49,430 --> 00:19:51,260
There was an additional passer. In a way,

336
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:53,230
that means he's the bottom-ranked contestant.

337
00:19:53,360 --> 00:19:54,429
How did you feel...

338
00:19:54,430 --> 00:19:56,670
when the bottom-ranked contestant joined your team?

339
00:20:01,940 --> 00:20:02,970
How I felt?

340
00:20:03,510 --> 00:20:05,080
I had mixed feelings about it.

341
00:20:09,280 --> 00:20:10,510
She's honest.

342
00:20:11,450 --> 00:20:13,320
You had mixed feelings. What about now?

343
00:20:13,420 --> 00:20:14,589
Now, I'm so glad.

344
00:20:14,590 --> 00:20:15,950
- Are you glad? - Yes.

345
00:20:16,850 --> 00:20:20,020
Is there a particular order we need to eat?

346
00:20:20,190 --> 00:20:23,560
We wanted to prepare the ingredients that suit the workout routine.

347
00:20:23,760 --> 00:20:25,559
So, we have morning apples,

348
00:20:25,560 --> 00:20:26,800
which are considered more precious than gold.

349
00:20:26,960 --> 00:20:28,330
Start your day with them.

350
00:20:32,700 --> 00:20:34,469
While you're working out,

351
00:20:34,470 --> 00:20:37,040
the sweet potatoes will increase your endurance.

352
00:20:37,140 --> 00:20:39,110
Continue with your day's workout with it.

353
00:20:41,450 --> 00:20:44,110
After a hard workout session, you lose muscles.

354
00:20:44,280 --> 00:20:46,379
To regain muscles fast,

355
00:20:46,380 --> 00:20:48,319
have some hummus and wrap up the workout.

356
00:20:48,320 --> 00:20:50,890
We've prepared our products with such ideas.

357
00:20:55,890 --> 00:20:57,930
It'll be great if you eat them in that order.

358
00:20:58,200 --> 00:20:59,830
- Okay. - He's a smooth talker.

359
00:21:01,330 --> 00:21:02,969
When you're tasting the breads,

360
00:21:02,970 --> 00:21:05,970
it'll be great to have them with the protein drink up here.

361
00:21:11,070 --> 00:21:13,140
It's flavorful and savory.

362
00:21:13,240 --> 00:21:15,150
- It's easy on the stomach. - Right?

363
00:21:15,210 --> 00:21:18,680
It's a protein drink packed with various nutrients.

364
00:21:39,100 --> 00:21:41,170
That team probably did a great job.

365
00:21:42,110 --> 00:21:44,439
They got quite a good evaluation from the Shopping Judges.

366
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:45,510
That's right.

367
00:22:12,770 --> 00:22:15,540
But is it okay to eat braised apple and candied sweet potato...

368
00:22:15,910 --> 00:22:19,040
when you work out regularly?

369
00:22:19,310 --> 00:22:21,379
While watching you make these pies,

370
00:22:21,380 --> 00:22:23,750
I figured they were for bulking up.

371
00:22:24,050 --> 00:22:25,680
I mean, they would definitely...

372
00:22:26,450 --> 00:22:27,579
make you gain weight.

373
00:22:27,580 --> 00:22:29,550
I couldn't stop thinking that.

374
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:52,839
Many people may think of weight loss when they hear our theme.

375
00:22:52,840 --> 00:22:55,479
But our intention was to make an energy booster...

376
00:22:55,480 --> 00:22:57,109
for those who do intensive workouts.

377
00:22:57,110 --> 00:23:00,079
It started with the concept of pies designed for muscle growth,

378
00:23:00,080 --> 00:23:02,620
which was the idea I suggested.

379
00:23:05,720 --> 00:23:08,560
I majored in nutritional science.

380
00:23:08,960 --> 00:23:11,899
It's true that high-calorie foods provide energy,

381
00:23:11,900 --> 00:23:15,670
but these pies seem to be too high in calories.

382
00:23:15,900 --> 00:23:18,600
All three of these pies are made with feuilletage.

383
00:23:19,700 --> 00:23:22,470
They all have cream on them. There are deep-fried sweet potatoes.

384
00:23:23,140 --> 00:23:24,810
The apples are braised with sugar.

385
00:23:25,680 --> 00:23:30,280
Therefore, all three of them felt very heavy.

386
00:23:31,920 --> 00:23:35,650
Also, the chocolate garnish feels a bit out of place.

387
00:23:36,650 --> 00:23:38,220
I thought it could've been better, but...

388
00:23:41,020 --> 00:23:44,730
I was nervous. I was shaking. It was nerve-racking.

389
00:23:45,330 --> 00:23:48,930
Also, when I saw these pies in the display case,

390
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:51,430
they looked the same as one another.

391
00:23:54,500 --> 00:23:55,939
They look so similar to one another. They're all yellow.

392
00:23:55,940 --> 00:23:59,410
The pastry is yellow, and so are the hummus and the sweet potatoes.

393
00:23:59,610 --> 00:24:01,310
Even the apples are yellow too.

394
00:24:06,580 --> 00:24:09,720
I expected a wider variety of flavors,

395
00:24:09,990 --> 00:24:12,419
but the sweetness overpowers the other flavors,

396
00:24:12,420 --> 00:24:13,720
and they're all quite greasy.

397
00:24:13,920 --> 00:24:17,530
So I don't think I can finish them at once.

398
00:24:18,660 --> 00:24:21,160
I had such mixed feelings.

399
00:24:21,970 --> 00:24:25,700
I realized that I should have done better.

400
00:24:26,640 --> 00:24:27,800
It seems like...

401
00:24:28,710 --> 00:24:32,140
it's hard to get positive feedback in Round Two either.

402
00:24:32,240 --> 00:24:34,480
Still, I hope you can find something special in our pies.

403
00:24:35,780 --> 00:24:39,780
We wanted to create products that would convince the Masters.

404
00:24:40,680 --> 00:24:42,620
But I think we failed to do so.

405
00:24:48,020 --> 00:24:49,589
- Are we next? - Yes.

406
00:24:49,590 --> 00:24:50,660
Now...

407
00:24:50,790 --> 00:24:53,060
Team Sunday Morning, please come forward.

408
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:57,270
Good luck.

409
00:24:59,370 --> 00:25:01,540
- Is it pain de campagne? - It looks like it.

410
00:25:01,940 --> 00:25:04,070
They're small and cute. They did a great job.

411
00:25:04,770 --> 00:25:06,040
Here you go.

412
00:25:06,380 --> 00:25:07,510
Thank you. I'll enjoy them.

413
00:25:11,550 --> 00:25:12,780
They're cute and pretty.

414
00:25:15,290 --> 00:25:17,190
We tried to create a heartwarming breakfast...

415
00:25:18,490 --> 00:25:20,560
that an entire family could enjoy together on a Sunday morning.

416
00:25:20,660 --> 00:25:23,530
We tried to find the perfect ingredient to create such a meal.

417
00:25:24,160 --> 00:25:27,230
And we chose Earl Grey as our main ingredient.

418
00:25:28,130 --> 00:25:32,540
We made three types of bread with sentimental themes.

419
00:25:34,870 --> 00:25:37,910
First up is Dad's Morning, which is a rye bread.

420
00:25:38,610 --> 00:25:42,710
With rye as the main ingredient, we added dried fruits.

421
00:25:42,980 --> 00:25:46,219
It's a bread for dads to enjoy as a fuss-free breakfast.

422
00:25:46,220 --> 00:25:48,650
With that concept, we created a nutty, aromatic bread.

423
00:25:50,190 --> 00:25:51,420
The second bread is...

424
00:25:51,790 --> 00:25:55,189
a brunch-style toast made using brioche...

425
00:25:55,190 --> 00:25:56,730
and black tea sauce.

426
00:25:57,260 --> 00:25:59,600
It's a bread for moms to enjoy.

427
00:26:01,260 --> 00:26:03,830
The third one is Children's Morning.

428
00:26:04,370 --> 00:26:08,770
By adding chocolate, macadamia, and hazelnut,

429
00:26:09,140 --> 00:26:10,910
we created a delicious bread roll.

430
00:26:12,240 --> 00:26:15,180
We'll taste the breads and evaluate them.

431
00:26:16,750 --> 00:26:18,880
I think I was sure...

432
00:26:19,080 --> 00:26:22,650
that they would like our breads once they tried them.

433
00:26:47,440 --> 00:26:48,480
Oh, no.

434
00:26:49,310 --> 00:26:50,350
We made a mistake.

435
00:26:52,220 --> 00:26:55,220
The bread wouldn't tear.

436
00:26:55,920 --> 00:26:57,690
Right then, I realized...

437
00:26:59,060 --> 00:27:01,460
that we started off on the wrong foot.

438
00:27:35,090 --> 00:27:38,560
You said your concept was a heartwarming Sunday breakfast.

439
00:27:39,200 --> 00:27:40,659
But rather than "heartwarming,"

440
00:27:40,660 --> 00:27:43,730
it's more like a "jaw-breaking" Sunday breakfast.

441
00:27:44,030 --> 00:27:49,609
The scent of Earl Grey harmonizes with the bread overall.

442
00:27:49,610 --> 00:27:52,640
Also, the sweetness is just right, and they taste good.

443
00:27:52,780 --> 00:27:55,779
But in terms of the texture,

444
00:27:55,780 --> 00:27:58,310
all your breads were too tough, in my opinion.

445
00:27:59,920 --> 00:28:03,690
You are the only team among all eight teams...

446
00:28:04,150 --> 00:28:06,890
that is made up entirely of bakers.

447
00:28:07,760 --> 00:28:10,160
However, I have a question I'd like to ask you.

448
00:28:11,560 --> 00:28:13,230
Have you tried working together?

449
00:28:13,600 --> 00:28:14,600
Pardon?

450
00:28:14,700 --> 00:28:18,270
Have the four of you worked together to make these breads...

451
00:28:19,070 --> 00:28:20,740
even just once?

452
00:28:24,210 --> 00:28:26,380
I assume that each of you created your own bread.

453
00:28:27,080 --> 00:28:29,350
Rather than creating bread that suits a pop-up store,

454
00:28:30,310 --> 00:28:33,920
it seems like you created the kind that you'd sell in your own bakery.

455
00:28:34,480 --> 00:28:37,420
That crossed my mind, and I wanted to point it out.

456
00:28:56,870 --> 00:28:59,310
Contender Oh Seung Geun.

457
00:28:59,510 --> 00:29:02,250
Don't you feel sad or disappointed about it?

458
00:29:02,780 --> 00:29:06,019
I believe that in a team, some must take the lead...

459
00:29:06,020 --> 00:29:09,150
while others support from behind.

460
00:29:09,550 --> 00:29:11,490
So I don't feel sad or disappointed.

461
00:29:12,960 --> 00:29:16,330
You said you didn't feel that way, but I'm very sad and disappointed.

462
00:29:16,560 --> 00:29:18,899
It's because you're one of the few contenders...

463
00:29:18,900 --> 00:29:22,329
out of all of the contenders...

464
00:29:22,330 --> 00:29:24,970
who impressed me so much...

465
00:29:25,440 --> 00:29:28,670
that I got goosebumps in Round One.

466
00:29:28,940 --> 00:29:30,840
So I had high expectations of you.

467
00:29:31,910 --> 00:29:34,409
But I don't see anything...

468
00:29:34,410 --> 00:29:36,850
that shows your baking style or your baking skills.

469
00:29:37,180 --> 00:29:40,350
So I wish you had found a way...

470
00:29:41,320 --> 00:29:42,490
to show your own style a little bit.

471
00:29:43,790 --> 00:29:45,960
Team Sunday Morning, thank you for your effort.

472
00:29:47,320 --> 00:29:50,160
- I understand. Thank you. - Thank you.

473
00:29:54,430 --> 00:29:56,800
Who will serve it to Chef Kim Narae?

474
00:29:57,570 --> 00:29:58,600
Chef Kim Narae?

475
00:30:01,240 --> 00:30:02,340
Shall I serve it to her?

476
00:30:04,470 --> 00:30:05,840
Give her the best one.

477
00:30:06,680 --> 00:30:07,879
Next up is...

478
00:30:07,880 --> 00:30:10,250
Team Pick-Me-Up Day, please come forward.

479
00:30:16,650 --> 00:30:18,960
It's interesting. Look at that.

480
00:30:19,520 --> 00:30:20,860
What? Is that a cream puff?

481
00:30:38,070 --> 00:30:39,579
Please tell us about your team...

482
00:30:39,580 --> 00:30:42,210
and the breads you made.

483
00:30:43,510 --> 00:30:46,780
Hello. We're Team Pick-Me-Up Day.

484
00:30:47,320 --> 00:30:48,720
When we heard the theme,

485
00:30:48,920 --> 00:30:52,320
the first thing that came to mind was the image of clouds.

486
00:30:53,220 --> 00:30:55,119
We thought of the feeling of floating in the sky.

487
00:30:55,120 --> 00:30:58,229
Our goal was to make breads that could lift your spirits...

488
00:30:58,230 --> 00:30:59,729
when you're feeling down.

489
00:30:59,730 --> 00:31:01,900
We wanted to make something that could lighten your mood.

490
00:31:02,270 --> 00:31:05,670
So we created breads that feature the theme of clouds.

491
00:31:06,940 --> 00:31:10,070
We made bouchee, mousse, and egg tart with cream puff.

492
00:31:10,640 --> 00:31:13,980
As for the bouchee,

493
00:31:15,650 --> 00:31:18,250
it's shaped like a cloud and has a fluffy texture.

494
00:31:18,680 --> 00:31:20,550
We tried to make our bouchee like a cloud.

495
00:31:27,690 --> 00:31:29,030
As for the egg tart with cream puff,

496
00:31:29,330 --> 00:31:33,300
we combined crunchy egg tart pastry and soft, airy puff pastry.

497
00:31:34,500 --> 00:31:36,900
The crunch of the egg tart pastry will make you happy.

498
00:31:37,270 --> 00:31:40,170
Next up is mousse with grapefruit...

499
00:31:40,370 --> 00:31:43,969
that can cheer you up when you're feeling gloomy.

500
00:31:43,970 --> 00:31:46,040
That's all for the introduction of our breads.

501
00:31:48,380 --> 00:31:50,910
Please try the bouchee first, then the egg tart,

502
00:31:51,180 --> 00:31:52,450
and finally the mousse.

503
00:31:52,750 --> 00:31:55,180
That's the best way to enjoy our breads.

504
00:31:55,720 --> 00:31:56,749
I understand.

505
00:31:56,750 --> 00:31:58,420
- Shall we taste them now? - Yes.

506
00:32:00,860 --> 00:32:01,920
Of course, I was nervous.

507
00:32:02,260 --> 00:32:04,789
Obviously, I wanted to receive positive feedback.

508
00:32:04,790 --> 00:32:06,960
My heart wouldn't stop pounding.

509
00:32:20,210 --> 00:32:22,179
Once you take a bite of it,

510
00:32:22,180 --> 00:32:25,520
you're supposed to feel an airy, cloud-like texture.

511
00:32:25,750 --> 00:32:27,380
I'm a little worried if it might not have that texture.

512
00:32:44,830 --> 00:32:47,399
As everyone else is still eating, I'll be the first...

513
00:32:47,400 --> 00:32:48,440
to evaluate the breads.

514
00:32:48,710 --> 00:32:52,239
To be honest, I was very...

515
00:32:52,240 --> 00:32:53,740
I was a bit surprised.

516
00:32:53,980 --> 00:32:58,410
These are the outcomes that showcase your genius.

517
00:33:01,180 --> 00:33:03,689
You didn't just shape your breads like clouds.

518
00:33:03,690 --> 00:33:06,420
The texture and mouthfeel...

519
00:33:06,760 --> 00:33:09,859
also bring the image of clouds to life...

520
00:33:09,860 --> 00:33:11,230
and that experience perfectly suits the cloud theme.

521
00:33:11,560 --> 00:33:13,730
I was impressed while eating them.

522
00:33:17,430 --> 00:33:20,699
You see, I know what you meant now that I've tasted them.

523
00:33:20,700 --> 00:33:23,469
It felt like they turned into clouds in my mouth.

524
00:33:23,470 --> 00:33:27,710
It was a fascinating experience.

525
00:33:28,310 --> 00:33:30,879
I really enjoyed them overall.

526
00:33:30,880 --> 00:33:31,880
Thank you.

527
00:33:32,750 --> 00:33:36,149
You did a great job with this sugar strip...

528
00:33:36,150 --> 00:33:39,020
showing your advanced skills as a seasoned contender.

529
00:33:41,620 --> 00:33:43,960
But a rainbow has seven colors starting with red.

530
00:33:44,430 --> 00:33:47,599
This one starts with blue. And then red, yellow...

531
00:33:47,600 --> 00:33:48,730
It ends with purple.

532
00:33:49,370 --> 00:33:52,239
- Let it slide. It's trivial. - Master Kim, come on.

533
00:33:52,240 --> 00:33:53,869
- I didn't even realize that. - Let it slide.

534
00:33:53,870 --> 00:33:55,409
My goodness. She's too strict.

535
00:33:55,410 --> 00:33:57,570
- Come on, Master Kim. - You could've done a better job...

536
00:33:58,310 --> 00:33:59,410
with such details like that.

537
00:34:03,280 --> 00:34:07,580
In my opinion, the shape of clouds...

538
00:34:07,720 --> 00:34:10,019
and the texture of the bouchee...

539
00:34:10,020 --> 00:34:12,560
could lighten a person's mood. However...

540
00:34:14,890 --> 00:34:17,630
The overall taste wasn't...

541
00:34:17,760 --> 00:34:20,800
quite enough to lift someone's spirits.

542
00:34:25,570 --> 00:34:27,099
They put cream cheese in all three of them.

543
00:34:27,100 --> 00:34:28,370
Right, they used cream cheese for all three of them.

544
00:34:28,770 --> 00:34:32,510
When it comes to the bouchee,

545
00:34:33,840 --> 00:34:35,810
it's baked really well.

546
00:34:42,920 --> 00:34:46,789
It becomes dry when it's cooked any longer than this.

547
00:34:46,790 --> 00:34:49,630
You found the optimal conditions to bake it to perfection.

548
00:34:50,490 --> 00:34:53,559
There are no dark spots on the bottom.

549
00:34:53,560 --> 00:34:56,970
And usually, it gets soggy when something goes wrong.

550
00:34:57,530 --> 00:34:59,369
It's very difficult to bake a bouchee...

551
00:34:59,370 --> 00:35:01,769
without burning the bottom...

552
00:35:01,770 --> 00:35:03,310
or making it too soggy.

553
00:35:04,170 --> 00:35:06,780
But you found the way to bake it perfectly.

554
00:35:07,780 --> 00:35:09,679
You baked a bouchee...

555
00:35:09,680 --> 00:35:11,510
without losing any moisture.

556
00:35:11,950 --> 00:35:14,879
- He seems happy. - I'd like to compliment you...

557
00:35:14,880 --> 00:35:15,990
for your baking techniques.

558
00:35:16,050 --> 00:35:17,390
I got a little emotional.

559
00:35:17,520 --> 00:35:20,489
I struggled a lot emotionally.

560
00:35:20,490 --> 00:35:23,590
And I practiced really hard to bake it.

561
00:35:41,680 --> 00:35:44,580
I think it suits a pop-up store...

562
00:35:45,050 --> 00:35:46,520
better than any other products.

563
00:35:46,750 --> 00:35:47,820
I really enjoyed it.

564
00:35:49,050 --> 00:35:51,350
- Great job. - Thank you.

565
00:35:55,760 --> 00:35:56,760
You know I'm right about this.

566
00:35:57,760 --> 00:35:59,100
This isn't a rainbow.

567
00:36:00,730 --> 00:36:01,830
It's more like a collection of national flags.

568
00:36:02,970 --> 00:36:04,169
Let it slide.

569
00:36:04,170 --> 00:36:06,370
- Gosh, come on. - My goodness.

570
00:36:10,470 --> 00:36:12,310
I should just relax.

571
00:36:12,610 --> 00:36:13,780
I'm nervous as it's a team match.

572
00:36:15,380 --> 00:36:16,580
I'm so nervous.

573
00:36:16,780 --> 00:36:18,549
- You'll go 1st, right? - I'll go 1st.

574
00:36:18,550 --> 00:36:19,650
All right.

575
00:36:21,120 --> 00:36:22,350
- Finally. - The last team.

576
00:36:23,420 --> 00:36:24,449
Good luck!

577
00:36:24,450 --> 00:36:25,859
- Thank you for waiting. - You've got this!

578
00:36:25,860 --> 00:36:29,130
- You've waited long too. - Delivery.

579
00:36:29,460 --> 00:36:31,960
- What did he say? - "Delivery."

580
00:36:33,760 --> 00:36:35,530
I really like the performance.

581
00:36:36,870 --> 00:36:39,800
It's amazing that Team Hangover Day figured out the theme.

582
00:36:40,140 --> 00:36:43,210
The team seemed to be making something sensational.

583
00:36:43,710 --> 00:36:45,040
I thought they were insanely creative.

584
00:36:45,780 --> 00:36:46,980
I can smell it right away.

585
00:36:55,750 --> 00:36:58,690
Hello. Thank you for waiting.

586
00:36:58,990 --> 00:37:01,390
The theme that my team chose is...

587
00:37:01,690 --> 00:37:03,960
the Hangover Day.

588
00:37:04,530 --> 00:37:06,129
"Bread as a hangover cure?"

589
00:37:06,130 --> 00:37:09,769
You may find it a bit strange and unfamiliar.

590
00:37:09,770 --> 00:37:11,299
All four of us thought...

591
00:37:11,300 --> 00:37:13,769
it was a good opportunity to develop a new type of bread...

592
00:37:13,770 --> 00:37:15,909
that we had never made before in our lives.

593
00:37:15,910 --> 00:37:19,939
We also decided to use this chance to let the world know...

594
00:37:19,940 --> 00:37:22,039
how charming Korean style bread could be.

595
00:37:22,040 --> 00:37:23,510
That was our mindset.

596
00:37:24,350 --> 00:37:27,880
The first bread we made is...

597
00:37:28,450 --> 00:37:30,590
Pork Backbone Hangover Bread.

598
00:37:30,990 --> 00:37:33,589
We pressure-cooked...

599
00:37:33,590 --> 00:37:35,389
backbone and pork shoulder...

600
00:37:35,390 --> 00:37:38,330
and then seasoned the meat with the sauce we made by ourselves.

601
00:37:38,760 --> 00:37:43,029
We stuffed bread with the typical ingredients...

602
00:37:43,030 --> 00:37:44,230
of gamjatang.

603
00:37:45,530 --> 00:37:49,810
The second bread we made is Buldak Seafood Bread.

604
00:37:50,740 --> 00:37:53,840
To cure a hangover, a touch of spiciness is essential.

605
00:37:54,680 --> 00:37:56,880
So we decided to use the buldak sauce.

606
00:37:57,450 --> 00:38:00,350
We stir-fried seafood with the sauce.

607
00:38:01,050 --> 00:38:04,620
It's a flavor loved by Gen Zers.

608
00:38:05,390 --> 00:38:10,230
The last bread we made is Italian Cheese Bread.

609
00:38:10,460 --> 00:38:13,729
When your stomach starts to burn with those spicy breads,

610
00:38:13,730 --> 00:38:16,099
the cheese in this bread will neutralize the spiciness.

611
00:38:16,100 --> 00:38:21,040
And we used tomatoes that are known as the best hangover cure.

612
00:38:21,400 --> 00:38:25,940
We added sun-dried tomatoes mixed with honey.

613
00:38:26,110 --> 00:38:28,379
The final touch that completes our product is...

614
00:38:28,380 --> 00:38:31,149
the cookie shaped like a ttukbaegi that's used as a plate...

615
00:38:31,150 --> 00:38:33,720
which makes your experience more enjoyable.

616
00:38:34,150 --> 00:38:36,520
To make you feel like you're eating hangover soup,

617
00:38:37,150 --> 00:38:40,720
we made a cookie in the shape of a ttukbaegi.

618
00:38:41,960 --> 00:38:43,190
You guys...

619
00:38:44,590 --> 00:38:46,760
didn't want this theme, did you?

620
00:38:46,960 --> 00:38:49,030
When I saw the theme,

621
00:38:49,500 --> 00:38:52,129
I thought it could be an interesting project.

622
00:38:52,130 --> 00:38:54,769
And I hoped no one would choose the theme.

623
00:38:54,770 --> 00:38:58,870
Chef Lee Kyung Mu here joined the team first.

624
00:38:59,610 --> 00:39:01,609
Since he had a ttukbaegi-like belly just like I did,

625
00:39:01,610 --> 00:39:04,509
I thought we should work together to make bread...

626
00:39:04,510 --> 00:39:05,719
that looked like a ttukbaegi.

627
00:39:05,720 --> 00:39:07,780
Which of the team members...

628
00:39:08,280 --> 00:39:12,789
was the mastermind behind the overall concept of your breads?

629
00:39:12,790 --> 00:39:15,090
We discussed and decided on the overall concept together.

630
00:39:15,590 --> 00:39:16,929
But the one who refined it...

631
00:39:16,930 --> 00:39:19,960
into the specific idea of "pork bone hangover soup..."

632
00:39:20,260 --> 00:39:22,260
was Chef Seong Min Su.

633
00:39:22,870 --> 00:39:24,799
You stayed there so quietly like the most unlikely suspect,

634
00:39:24,800 --> 00:39:26,870
but you were the one who came up with the idea.

635
00:39:27,470 --> 00:39:29,940
The ideas each of us came up with aren't as important as our teamwork.

636
00:39:30,110 --> 00:39:32,439
We helped one another and worked together as a team,

637
00:39:32,440 --> 00:39:33,910
which helped a lot.

638
00:39:36,410 --> 00:39:37,410
I understand.

639
00:39:37,411 --> 00:39:40,920
Now we'll taste the breads and talk about them.

640
00:39:55,870 --> 00:39:57,170
It really tastes like pork bone hangover soup.

641
00:40:23,960 --> 00:40:26,760
My, it's spicy. It's really spicy.

642
00:40:35,140 --> 00:40:36,510
They didn't seem very happy.

643
00:40:37,040 --> 00:40:40,110
And that made me feel even more anxious.

644
00:40:42,880 --> 00:40:46,180
When we first saw the theme,

645
00:40:48,480 --> 00:40:50,990
we were like, "What are they going to do?"

646
00:40:51,150 --> 00:40:52,960
One of you was boiling meat...

647
00:40:53,790 --> 00:40:55,660
while another was boiling a squid.

648
00:40:57,560 --> 00:41:00,600
I was worried about how you'd remove the unpleasant odors.

649
00:41:03,700 --> 00:41:05,970
We tasted it after it had cooled down.

650
00:41:06,340 --> 00:41:09,100
It was cold, but there were no unpleasant odors at all.

651
00:41:10,210 --> 00:41:11,240
By the way...

652
00:41:11,610 --> 00:41:13,109
They managed to remove the unpleasant odors.

653
00:41:13,110 --> 00:41:14,740
Exactly. I thought of that too.

654
00:41:17,010 --> 00:41:19,820
You did a great job at removing the odors.

655
00:41:20,220 --> 00:41:21,280
Also...

656
00:41:23,420 --> 00:41:26,459
The ingredients don't seem like they would work together,

657
00:41:26,460 --> 00:41:27,719
but they actually do,

658
00:41:27,720 --> 00:41:29,189
which fascinates me.

659
00:41:29,190 --> 00:41:32,360
I really enjoyed this fascinating bread.

660
00:41:33,060 --> 00:41:34,500
- Thank you. - Thank you.

661
00:41:36,070 --> 00:41:38,570
I had said this even before we came out here.

662
00:41:38,800 --> 00:41:40,400
"It'll be awesome if this one tastes good."

663
00:41:40,670 --> 00:41:41,740
"It'll be amazing."

664
00:41:43,240 --> 00:41:45,569
If I had only Italian Cheese Bread,

665
00:41:45,570 --> 00:41:46,940
I would've found it too greasy.

666
00:41:47,180 --> 00:41:50,179
But as I ate Italian Cheese Bread after eating the spicy breads,

667
00:41:50,180 --> 00:41:52,550
it perfectly refreshed my palate.

668
00:41:52,880 --> 00:41:54,179
Then I was ready to start all over again.

669
00:41:54,180 --> 00:41:56,090
And I felt like I could keep eating them forever.

670
00:41:57,690 --> 00:42:00,220
I really enjoyed your breads. Thank you.

671
00:42:01,790 --> 00:42:04,959
If I had to provide an example...

672
00:42:04,960 --> 00:42:08,329
of the direction K-bakery should take...

673
00:42:08,330 --> 00:42:09,729
to explain its future to many people,

674
00:42:09,730 --> 00:42:13,800
your breads would be the best choice.

675
00:42:14,170 --> 00:42:16,170
We received positive feedback,

676
00:42:16,610 --> 00:42:18,370
and I was overwhelmed with joy.

677
00:42:18,570 --> 00:42:19,910
Well...

678
00:42:20,980 --> 00:42:23,410
They all have different opinions from mine,

679
00:42:23,850 --> 00:42:25,710
which surprises me, to be honest.

680
00:42:29,590 --> 00:42:32,590
The most important thing about savory desserts is the saltiness.

681
00:42:33,090 --> 00:42:34,720
And the levels of saltiness are inconsistent.

682
00:42:36,830 --> 00:42:39,190
The Pork Backbone Hangover Bread is too bland...

683
00:42:39,830 --> 00:42:43,199
while the squid is a bit too salty.

684
00:42:43,200 --> 00:42:45,570
And the squid and shrimp were overcooked.

685
00:42:46,940 --> 00:42:48,740
The moment I heard him say that, I was disheartened.

686
00:42:49,740 --> 00:42:53,880
Buldak Seafood Bread was supposed to have bean sprouts in it,

687
00:42:54,740 --> 00:42:56,680
but we forgot to bring it.

688
00:42:56,850 --> 00:42:59,420
I'll prepare the vegetables.

689
00:43:03,520 --> 00:43:04,550
What?

690
00:43:08,660 --> 00:43:09,729
- Hey. - Yes?

691
00:43:09,730 --> 00:43:11,130
Are there no bean sprouts?

692
00:43:11,260 --> 00:43:13,160
- Bean sprouts? - Yes.

693
00:43:14,960 --> 00:43:18,630
Bean sprouts... I think I left it.

694
00:43:21,370 --> 00:43:22,599
Do we need bean sprouts?

695
00:43:22,600 --> 00:43:24,370
Yes. We need it for the seafood bread.

696
00:43:25,470 --> 00:43:27,810
I removed it thinking we didn't need it.

697
00:43:28,880 --> 00:43:29,910
What should we do?

698
00:43:30,250 --> 00:43:31,450
I felt so bad.

699
00:43:32,280 --> 00:43:35,990
It could affect our evaluation.

700
00:43:36,390 --> 00:43:39,660
We tried to replace it using something else.

701
00:43:54,500 --> 00:43:56,169
The result of the mission, A Good Day for Bread,

702
00:43:56,170 --> 00:43:59,110
is in my hands.

703
00:43:59,380 --> 00:44:01,780
Which teams will survive as whole teams...

704
00:44:02,640 --> 00:44:05,050
and which team will fail as the whole team?

705
00:44:06,020 --> 00:44:07,719
After totaling 500 points from the Masters...

706
00:44:07,720 --> 00:44:11,490
and 100 points from the Shopping Judges...

707
00:44:16,830 --> 00:44:17,860
I will...

708
00:44:19,330 --> 00:44:20,530
reveal it now.

709
00:44:23,170 --> 00:44:26,040
I never thought I'd be eliminated.

710
00:44:26,640 --> 00:44:28,069
My team definitely won.

711
00:44:28,070 --> 00:44:29,200
I won't accept anything else.

712
00:44:29,710 --> 00:44:31,210
- Let's win second place. - Second place.

713
00:44:31,440 --> 00:44:32,440
No, first place.

714
00:44:35,340 --> 00:44:39,050
First, I'll reveal the team which all members passed,

715
00:44:40,120 --> 00:44:43,220
the team that won first place.

716
00:44:44,050 --> 00:44:45,050
First place.

717
00:44:45,990 --> 00:44:47,089
After listening to the judges' comments,

718
00:44:47,090 --> 00:44:49,730
I genuinely thought we would win first place.

719
00:44:50,760 --> 00:44:51,789
This is amazing.

720
00:44:51,790 --> 00:44:54,259
- This would definitely work. - I think...

721
00:44:54,260 --> 00:44:57,729
this is the most suitable vision...

722
00:44:57,730 --> 00:45:01,800
of how K-bakery should develop.

723
00:45:02,400 --> 00:45:05,769
You can feel certain things from what the Masters say.

724
00:45:05,770 --> 00:45:07,710
It's your gut feeling.

725
00:45:07,810 --> 00:45:09,210
I was quite surprised.

726
00:45:09,450 --> 00:45:13,150
- I could see the genius. - It's very well-baked.

727
00:45:13,520 --> 00:45:17,590
You baked bouchee while capturing all the moisture.

728
00:45:18,150 --> 00:45:21,190
I really liked how balanced the taste and smell are.

729
00:45:21,260 --> 00:45:23,990
It was better than expected in terms of balance.

730
00:45:25,730 --> 00:45:28,800
I thought we must win 1st or 2nd place, no matter what.

731
00:45:30,030 --> 00:45:34,540
Which team will place first and all the teammates will survive?

732
00:45:42,040 --> 00:45:45,550
Scoring 473 points in total...

733
00:45:57,760 --> 00:45:58,860
Congratulations.

734
00:45:59,130 --> 00:46:00,930
It's Team Pick-Me-Up Day.

735
00:46:03,400 --> 00:46:04,470
Congratulations.

736
00:46:05,470 --> 00:46:08,500
It's Team Pick-Me-Up Day. Congratulations.

737
00:46:17,210 --> 00:46:18,310
Oh, my gosh.

738
00:46:18,480 --> 00:46:20,420
Thank you.

739
00:46:20,850 --> 00:46:22,819
Good job.

740
00:46:22,820 --> 00:46:24,089
Good job.

741
00:46:24,090 --> 00:46:26,120
- Good job. - Good job, really.

742
00:46:29,320 --> 00:46:31,260
They worked so hard.

743
00:46:31,330 --> 00:46:33,260
- He's crying. - This is touching.

744
00:46:33,800 --> 00:46:35,560
- He's crying. - I can understand.

745
00:46:44,240 --> 00:46:45,770
Did you touch the cake with your hand?

746
00:46:47,540 --> 00:46:48,680
I was in a rush, so...

747
00:46:50,110 --> 00:46:51,850
I messed it up big time near the end.

748
00:46:55,780 --> 00:46:57,590
I'm so sorry to my teammates.

749
00:46:58,690 --> 00:46:59,960
I felt so bad.

750
00:47:01,460 --> 00:47:03,060
I won't forget this debt.

751
00:47:11,670 --> 00:47:14,970
Next, I'll announce the team that won second place,

752
00:47:15,170 --> 00:47:17,370
which all the team members will survive.

753
00:47:19,980 --> 00:47:24,350
The team that came in second and will survive as a whole...

754
00:47:25,110 --> 00:47:29,790
scored a total of 472 points.

755
00:47:30,520 --> 00:47:31,520
It's only one point difference.

756
00:47:40,430 --> 00:47:42,230
It's Team Hangover Day.

757
00:47:42,460 --> 00:47:44,469
It's Team Hangover Day.

758
00:47:44,470 --> 00:47:45,500
Congratulations.

759
00:47:50,670 --> 00:47:51,710
One point difference.

760
00:47:52,470 --> 00:47:54,140
That team did well.

761
00:47:55,980 --> 00:48:00,080
You came in 2nd, just 1 point behind the winning team.

762
00:48:03,550 --> 00:48:04,620
I was so surprised.

763
00:48:06,590 --> 00:48:09,160
It felt like we barely made it alive.

764
00:48:09,690 --> 00:48:12,190
It's the rebellion of the losers.

765
00:48:12,260 --> 00:48:13,660
I felt elated.

766
00:48:14,130 --> 00:48:18,070
It was as if we were rewarded for all our hard work and trouble.

767
00:48:18,400 --> 00:48:19,570
I felt so happy.

768
00:48:23,010 --> 00:48:25,340
Moving on, I'll announce third place.

769
00:48:28,740 --> 00:48:30,449
For your information, all of you have the chance...

770
00:48:30,450 --> 00:48:31,580
of getting eliminated.

771
00:48:33,220 --> 00:48:34,220
Third place goes to...

772
00:48:34,920 --> 00:48:37,050
Team Flirting Day.

773
00:48:39,150 --> 00:48:42,690
In fourth place is Team Picnic Day.

774
00:48:43,360 --> 00:48:44,960
Next, fifth place.

775
00:48:45,360 --> 00:48:47,360
It goes to Team Cheat Day.

776
00:48:49,130 --> 00:48:50,230
Next,

777
00:48:50,500 --> 00:48:53,200
Team Dopamine Day is in sixth place.

778
00:48:54,270 --> 00:48:55,400
That's us.

779
00:49:04,280 --> 00:49:07,620
Third place onward means you could get eliminated.

780
00:49:08,320 --> 00:49:09,720
Could it really be because of that?

781
00:49:09,950 --> 00:49:11,550
Did this really happen...

782
00:49:12,050 --> 00:49:14,720
because we added the rum just a tiny bit less?

783
00:49:15,360 --> 00:49:16,390
I was disappointed.

784
00:49:17,490 --> 00:49:18,930
This is unexpected.

785
00:49:19,960 --> 00:49:22,700
My heart sank. We really thought we'd place 1st or 2nd.

786
00:49:29,240 --> 00:49:31,810
Now, there are...

787
00:49:32,040 --> 00:49:34,210
only two teams left.

788
00:49:34,740 --> 00:49:37,250
For 1 of the 2 teams, the whole team will be eliminated.

789
00:49:37,780 --> 00:49:41,420
They must leave the bread factory as soon as the result is announced.

790
00:49:42,820 --> 00:49:44,950
I hoped we'd place seventh.

791
00:49:45,490 --> 00:49:49,020
I think this is too high in calories.

792
00:49:49,590 --> 00:49:53,959
